          <change when="2017-08-09T16:43:40+02:00"
                 who="http://papyri.info/users/JacquesBromberg">Submit - Added metadata and Greek text, NY workshop. I made the following changes to the edition in O. Claud 2.409:&#xD;
&#xD;
Line 1: Edition prints “υ” as wholly visible at beginning of line, which it is not. While the word is surely Θαυμάσιον, in fact only -μάσιον is clear, so I have written “υ̣”.&#xD;
Line 2: I supply “[ν]” at beginning of line, which is extremely likely following “σθε-” at the end of line 1.&#xD;
Line 5: Edition prints initial “ν” as unclear (“]ν̣εσιαις”), but in fact the letter is almost entirely lost (and the visible bit does not look to me like a “ν”), so I have written “].εσιαις” and added an editorial note that even Cockle is uncertain about it.&#xD;
Line 7: Edition prints initial “π” in πεποθημένε as visible on the ostracon, but (though almost certain) it is very unclear, so I have written “] π̣εποθημένε”.&#xD;
Line 8: Edition prints initial “ο” as clear on the ostracon, but (though almost certain) it is only partially preserved, so I have indicated as “ο̣”.&#xD;
Line 9: I have supplied [ν] at the beginning of the line, which is almost certain following κινδυ- at the end of line 8.&#xD;
Line 10: Edition does not recognize initial “μ” (prints blank under-dot), though it is partially visible, so I have written “μ̣ολως”&#xD;
Line 13: Edition does not recognize initial letter (prints blank under-dot), but again “μ” is partially preserved, so I have written “μ̣η”.&#xD;</change>
